    <center><h1>Back to
    School...</h1></center>

    <a href = "/1size.html">Click Here to Start Designing a COVID-19 Safe Classroom</a>
    <p>As the schools begin to open across the nation, teachers, students, and parents alike are beginning to navigate COVID-19 concerns in the classroom. 

    <center><h3>Why We Made This</h3></center>
    <p>We understand how difficult this time has been for educators as there is a lot of change involved. We are hoping to just make this process as easy as possible for teachers.</p>
  
    <center><h3>COVID-19 Guidlines Resources By State</h3></center>
    <p>Below  listed are links to COVID-19 guidelines corresponding to each state. It is of utmost importance to stay informed and aware of the current COVID-19 situtaions occuring in your respective state, as well as the world, for the safety of all people.</p>
    <h5>DISCLAIMER: The Classroom Social Distancing Simulator is created using CDC guidelines updated as of 7/24/2020.</h5>

 

